      <item>
        <title>How to use icons properly?</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[mburridge]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hi <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/inamkbmail">@inamkbmail</a></p>
<p>Here’s a couple of approaches. Font Awesome allows you to create subsets of icons to reduce file size and even just import the icons you need into your project. Take a look at:</p>
<p><a href="https://fontawesome.com/how-to-use/with-the-api/setup/library" class="onebox" target="_blank">https://fontawesome.com/how-to-use/with-the-api/setup/library</a></p>
<p>Another possibility is to create the svg/jpeg/png icons you need and store them in an <code>assets</code> folder. See <a href="https://github.com/chakra-ui/frontity-chakra-ui-theme">https://github.com/chakra-ui/frontity-chakra-ui-theme</a> for an example of this approach.</p>
<p>Hope this helps.</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/how-to-use-icons-properly/1442/6">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
